The paper focuses on the effects of worker interactions in crowdsourcing environments, which is a topic related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also experiments with various types of tasks on crowdsourcing platforms, including image labeling (cs.CY), optical character recognition (OCR) (cs.CL), audio transcription (cs.IR), and nutrition analysis (cs.LG). Therefore, these sub-categories are likely to be relevant to the paper.
